<section class="essay section" aria-label="About Waseem Ilyas">
  <div class="shell">
    <div class="casehead" data-cal>
      <span class="ref">ABOUT</span>
      <h1>A technologist who designs, builds, teaches, and automates.</h1>
    </div>

    <p class="lede-essay" data-cal>I have been making digital things for over fifteen years. The thread that connects all of it is turning technology into something people can actually use.</p>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="prose" data-cal>
        <p>It started with graphic design at age 15: logos, branding, event and web work. That creative practice is still in the toolkit, but it is the origin story, not the centre of gravity.</p>
        <p>I studied Computer Science, worked as a front-end web developer at SportsShoes, then built a digital practice single-handedly at Global Diversity Practice: instructional design, e-learning production with Articulate Rise and Storyline, and the design of workshops and leadership programmes.</p>
        <p>Today I run <a href="/automancer/">Automancer</a>, a UK automation consultancy. I help small businesses get real value from AI and practical digital systems, without the cost and complexity of enterprise software. The work is hands-on: I scope the problem, design a lightweight system, and build it.</p>
        <p>Across all of it the register is the same. Precise, practical, and quietly confident. Technology that earns its place.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="datasheet" data-cal aria-label="At a glance">
        <div class="dh">At a glance</div>
